                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d100">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/8–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-19T21:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 19, 1945—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 29—8:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>870. Department’s telegram 3754 to Paris, repeated Athens as 799, August 9, and
                    my telegram 852, August 17.<note n="99" xml:id="d100fn99">Telegram 852 not
                        printed.</note> No word yet received from Paris and French colleague here
                    uninstructed. However, Prime Minister assured British colleague and me today
                    Greek Govt gladly accepts idea of tripartite supervision and even Anglo-United
                    States supervision if France now feels unable participate. Moscow informed in
                    accord your telegram 827, August 18 by repeat this message.</p>
                <p>Prime Minister promised continue take no initiative publicity but to await
                    official statements London Washington and be guided by any alterations these may
                    necessitate (e.g. as regards the French) in the <pb facs="0159" n="147"
                        xml:id="pg_147"/> proposed British-United States press announcements, copies
                    of which were handed him.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept as 870; repeated Moscow as 5; London as 90 and Paris as 3.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
